<div class="indented"><a id="comment-4296583"></a>


<div class="non_toggle_area" id="comment-4296583">
  <div class="non_toggle_label">
       <span class="scomments_info">Fri, 01/03/2014 - 12:12 | <a href="/news/2014-01-03/sign-top-hedge-fund-hiring-junior-bitcoin-execution-trader#comment-4296583" class="active">4296583</a></span>
              <b><a href="/users/thehound73" title="View user profile.">TheHound73</a></b>
  </div>

  <div class="comment-content">
    <div class="author"><div class="picture">
  <a href="/users/thehound73" title="View user profile."><img src="http://www.zerohedge.com/sites/default/files/pictures/picture-159269.png" alt="TheHound73&#039;s picture" title="TheHound73&#039;s picture"  /></a></div>
</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>Very difficult in a trust-less decentralized manner. &nbsp;For starters, it requires the distributed blockchain ledger. &nbsp;The problem is trivial to manage for a centralized service like PayPal.</p>
<p>&nbsp;<a href="http://blogs.cornell.edu/info4220/2013/03/29/bitcoin-and-the-double-spending-problem/" rel="nofollow">http://blogs.cornell.edu/info4220/2013/03/29/bitcoin-and-the-double-spending-problem/</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

  </div>
  <div class="links"><ul class="links"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul></div>
</div>
