    <p>So I woke up early and was curious and looked into Bitcoin mining this morning.</p>
<p>Most of the sites and links of information were dated 2011 and had not been updated.</p>
<p>I went to the mining calculator and found that my six-core desktop with an ATI HD 2GB video card would make .04 cents for every .36 cents I spent in electricity.</p>
<p>So yes, the crryptocurrency has entered the speculative bubble phase now that the small individual players have been priced out.</p>
<p>Just wait until Wall Street gets their high end servers and direct connections hashing block-chains while hawking 3X up/down ETF's and selling BBS (Bitcoin Backed Seurities); hoo-boy.</p>

